author: COMSOL
description: A solidly mounted resonator (SMR) is a MEMS piezoelectric resonator made from multiple layers of materials. This tutorial shows how Uncertainty Quantification is used to study the effect of manufacturing variation on the resonance frequency of the SMR. The tutorial shows how Sensitivity Analysis, Uncertainty Propagation, and Reliability Analysis are used in conjunction with an Eigenfrequency study.
label: solidly_mounted_resonator_2d_uncertainty_quantification.mph
